
[1]optimism

   OP'TIMISM, n. [L. optimus, best.] The opinion or doctrine that every
   thing in nature is ordered for the best; or the order of things in the
   universe that is adapted to produce the most good.

   The true and amiable philosophy of optimism.

   A system of strict optimism may be the real system in both cases.
